Note: "ssh-keygen" created a "FINGERPRINT" on public/private pair,
      it because we can compare different key pairs easily!
      it just hash the public key and generate shorter value like   SHA256:a8QjSiLdT8paNjNK69nJUqxvWJ8OQAm4JyFto9r+RXY first public/private key
      it also generate a picture to make it even easier!            (just for comparing two different pairs)

Note: "FINGERPRINT" created based on public key (it has not any clue about private part)
      we can create him by using public or private key,
      but the result will same and just introduce public key!

      ssh-keygen -lf firstKey.pub   //create fingerprint
      ssh-keygen -lf firstKey       //create fingerprint same as before!

Note: we find private/public keys files by terminal
      at first we lost them!

      find ~ -name "firstKey*" 2>/dev/null      // ~ to explore all the directories
                                                // "firstKey*" means name started by "firstKey"


Note: 2>/dev/null means
      just don't show errors like "find: /some/path: Permission denied"
      just show if you find!

      0 = standard input
      1 = standard output
      2 = standard error    //so 2 introduce errors

      ">" means redirect them

      2>/dev/null means redirect error to "/dev/null"
      it is black hole directory!
      This is a special file in Unix/macOS.
      Anything sent to /dev/null is discarded.